					<description><![CDATA[Background to the Legislation The Central Bank of Kenya (Amendment) Act, 2021 (hereinafter, “the Act”) is the latest development in the quickly evolving digital lending space in Kenya. Over the past decade or so, Kenya has achieved significant financial inclusion thanks to increased penetration into the market brought about by advances such as mobile banking, [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="pl-56803"  class="panel-layout" ><div id="pg-56803-0"  class="panel-grid panel-has-style" ><div class="panel-row-style panel-row-style-for-56803-0" ><div id="pgc-56803-0-0"  class="panel-grid-cell" ><div id="panel-56803-0-0-0" class="so-panel widget widget_sow-button panel-first-child panel-last-child widgetopts-SO" data-index="0" ><div class="panel-widget-style panel-widget-style-for-56803-0-0-0" ><div class="so-widget-sow-button so-widget-sow-button-flat-208f1388be32-56803"><div class="ow-button-base ow-button-align-left">
	<a href="https://www.oraro.co.ke/legal-alerts/" class="ow-icon-placement-left ow-button-hover" 		>
		<span>
			<span class="sow-icon-fontawesome sow-fas" data-sow-icon="&#xf104;"
		style="color: #955b2f" ></span>
